A proper new ballad on the old Parliament Or, the second part of Knave out of doores. To the tune of Hei ho my honey, my heart shall never rue, four and twenty now for your mony, and yet a hard pennyworth too.
1 sheet ([1] p.)
s.n., [London : 1659]
Verse - "Good morrow my neighbours all, what news is this I heard tell?". Imprint from Wing. Annotation on Thomason copy: "9ber [i.e. November]. 11. 1659". Reproduction of the originals in the British Library.
